<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <header>
      <div>
        <h1>GPAYSUP – Global Payments Escalation (JIRA) | Flow Chart</h1>
        <div class="subtitle">
          Executive-friendly intake-to-resolution flow: single global entry, automated validation + routing, clear SME ownership, SLA-driven closure.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="badgeRow">
        <div class="badge"><strong>Scope:</strong> Global</div>
        <div class="badge"><strong>Tool:</strong> JIRA</div>
        <div class="badge"><strong>Start:</strong> Intake (Program / Ops)</div>
        <div class="badge"><strong>End:</strong> Resolution</div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="card">
      <div class="topbar">
        <div class="title"><span class="dot"></span> End-to-End Escalation Flow</div>
        <div class="legend">
          <span class="key"><span class="sw a"></span>System</span>
          <span class="key"><span class="sw g"></span>SME Ownership</span>
          <span class="key"><span class="sw w"></span>Dependencies</span>
          <span class="key"><span class="sw d"></span>Risk / Escalation</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow">
        <div class="grid">
          <!-- Main spine -->
          <ol class="spine">
            <li class="node accent">
              <div class="kicker">
                <span>Step 1</span>
                <span class="pill">Intake</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Submit GPAYSUP Escalation (Program / Operations / Stakeholder)</h3>
              <p>Standardized “Global Payments Escalation” JIRA form with required payment details + evidence.</p>
            </li>

            <li class="node accent">
              <div class="kicker">
                <span>Step 2</span>
                <span class="pill">System</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Auto Validation + SLA Clock Start</h3>
              <p>Completeness checks (IDs, priority, required fields). Bliss linkage required if escalated from Tier-1.</p>
            </li>

            <li class="node accent">
              <div class="kicker">
                <span>Step 3</span>
                <span class="pill">System</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Automated Routing & Ownership Assignment</h3>
              <p>Routes by Entity, LOB, Country/Region, Category, Priority → assigns correct Payments SME/POC queue.</p>
            </li>

            <li class="node green">
              <div class="kicker">
                <span>Step 4</span>
                <span class="pill">SME</span>
              </div>
              <h3>First Response (TTFR) + Status Update</h3>
              <p>SME acknowledges, sets status <b>In Progress</b>, and logs first-touch actions + stakeholder comms.</p>
            </li>

            <li class="node green">
              <div class="kicker">
                <span>Step 5</span>
                <span class="pill">SME</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Investigation & Fix</h3>
              <p>Validate payment lifecycle (Authorized/Captured/Reversed/Failed), check tools/PSP, coordinate cross-team if needed.</p>
            </li>

            <li class="node warn">
              <div class="kicker">
                <span>Step 6</span>
                <span class="pill">Conditional</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Dependency Handling (If Required)</h3>
              <p>Use the right status to keep SLA + audit trail accurate (reporter, cross-team support, risk escalation).</p>
            </li>

            <li class="node green">
              <div class="kicker">
                <span>Step 7</span>
                <span class="pill">SME</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Resolution Documented</h3>
              <p>Root cause + corrective action recorded. Move to <b>Pending Review</b> once the fix is confirmed.</p>
            </li>

            <li class="node green">
              <div class="kicker">
                <span>Step 8</span>
                <span class="pill">Close</span>
              </div>
              <h3>Closure + Governance</h3>
              <p>Status <b>Closed</b>. SLA adherence captured; metrics feed dashboards (TTFR, TTR, misrouting, repeat escalations).</p>
            </li>
          </ol>

          <!-- Branches panel -->
          <aside class="branch">
            <h4><span>↳</span>Conditional Status Paths (Used During Step 6)</h4>
            <div class="branchGrid">
              <div class="branchItem warn">
                <b>Waiting on Reporter</b>
                <small>Missing info, confirmation needed, or requester action required. SLA risk visibility remains clear.</small>
              </div>
              <div class="branchItem warn">
                <b>Awaiting Assistance</b>
                <small>Cross-team dependency (e.g., PSP, regional ops, tool owners). Track timestamps and updates.</small>
              </div>
              <div class="branchItem danger">
                <b>Escalated</b>
                <small>High risk/complexity (P0, regulatory risk, severe disruption). Ensure leadership visibility and tighter updates.</small>
              </div>
              <div class="branchItem">
                <b>Reopened</b>
                <small>Issue persists or recurs after closure. Link prior ticket and document delta/root cause.</small>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="footerNote">
              <div class="cta">
                <b style="color:var(--text); font-weight:600;">Executive takeaway:</b>
                <span style="color:var(--muted);">Single intake → auto-route → single owner → SLA-driven resolution.</span>
              </div>
              <div style="opacity:0.9;">Statuses are timestamped & auditable in JIRA.</div>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</body>
